The paper deals with image stitching, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves formulating the warp as a bivariate system, which suggests the use of mathematical modeling and optimization techniques, making cs.MM (mathematical modeling) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the use of global similarity warps, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.AI) and pattern recognition (cs.LG).
